I'm a great believer in machines being named the same as their FQDN.  It
makes setting them up for Internet mail easy.

Of course, it doesn't *really* matter what the machine calls itself (in
gethostname(2)), as long as it behaves properly on its various
communications links.

I guess I'd argue that the machine's UUCP name, and thus its name in the
maps, should also be a FQDN.

		Craig

